         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">31/1/87 ¶  ¶ The genuine  ¶ Thysanotus dichotomus ¶ , dear Mr Tepper, does not have tubers but only a thick rhizome; but will certainly look at the whole group again soon from additional material, as ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">87.01.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M198, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Tepper: 'Reply Jan 24. 87'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>3/1/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Der ächte <name key="Thysanotus%20dichotomus">Thysanotus dichotomus</name>, lieber Herr Tepper, hat keine Knollen, sondern nur einen dicken Wurzelstock; will aber doch die ganze Gruppe bald wieder nach vermehrtem Material durchsuchen, da ja mehr wie eine Art von Bentham zusammengefasst sein mag, wie bei <name key="Centipeda">Centipeda</name>, u ich mich so habe vielleicht täuschen lassen.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Immer Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Die kleine Billardiera scheint Zwergform von B. cymosa mit einzelnen Blüthen zu sein.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nach Mr E.J. Brown soll gelegentlich eine neue südaustr Pfl. (wenn möglich Baum) Edwiniana genannt werden.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Der ächte <name key="Thysanotus%20tuberosus">Thysanotus tuberosus</name> hat immer spindelförmige Knollen. Ich mag in der Eile die <name key="Hibbertia">Hibbertia</name>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">verkannt</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> haben; das Benennen geschieht oft in Nachtstunden mit ermudeten u älternden Augen!</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Die Frucht (reif) müsste etweige Unterschiede der Billardieen</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>w<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Billardieren?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> zeigen. Die neue <name key="Lhotzkya">Lhotzkya</name> geht morgen in Druck hier. Besten Dank für Ihre prächtigen entomologischen Notizen.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">31/1/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The genuine <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Thysanotus%20dichotomus">Thysanotus dichotomus</name>
               </seg>, dear Mr Tepper, does not have tubers but only a thick rhizome; but will certainly look at the whole group again soon from additional material, as there may indeed be more than one species combined by Bentham, such as in the case of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Centipeda">Centipeda</name>
               </seg>, and perhaps I have allowed myself to be deceived.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The small <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Billardiera</seg> seems to be a dwarf form of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">B. cymosa</seg> with solitary flowers.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A new South Australian plant (if possible a tree) shall be named Edwiniana after Mr E. J. Brown<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John Ednie Brown?</p>
               </note> when there is an opportunity.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The genuine <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Thysanotus%20tuberosus">Thysanotus tuberosus</name>
               </seg> always has fusiform tubers. In the hurry I may have <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">misjudged</hi>
               </seg> the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Hibbertia">Hibbertia</name>
               </seg>; the naming often happens in the night hours with tired and ageing eyes.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The fruit (ripe) ought to show possible differences of [Billardierae]. The new <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Lhotzkya">Lhotzkya</name>
               </seg> goes to press here tomorrow.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In B87.01.02, issued on 20 January 1887.</p>
               </note> Best thanks for your splendid entomological notes.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Billardiera%20cymosa">Billardiera cymosa</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Centipeda">Centipeda</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hibbertia">Hibbertia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Lhotzkya">Lhotzkya</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Thysanotus%20dichotomus">Thysanotus dichotomus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Thysanotus%20tuberosus">Thysanotus tuberosus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
